.582Z", "updated_at": "2026-01-30T20:04:48.586Z", "views": 11, "likes": [], "dislikes": []}}, {"model": "blogs.blog", "pk": 11, "fields": {"title": "Ghjfgh", "slug": "ghjfgh-11", "category": null, "author": 1, "featured_image": "", "short_description": "ghjk", "blog_body": "<p><img alt=\"\" src=\"/media/uploads/2026/02/02/not-install_m3ZfDvk.png\" style=\"height:1140px; width:1920px\" /></p>", "status": "Published", "is_featured": false, "created_at": "2026-02-02T08:13:13.077Z", "updated_at": "2026-02-03T14:11:10.170Z", "views": 4, "likes": [], "dislikes": []}}, {"model": "blogs.blog", "pk": 14, "fields": {"title": "Demo", "slug": "demo-14", "category": 1, "author": 1, "featured_image": "image/upload/uploads/2026/02/04/not_install.png", "short_description": "dfv", "blog_body": "<p>df</p>", "status": "Published", "is_featured": true, "created_at": "2026-02-04T12:35:02.116Z", "updated_at": "2026-02-04T12:35:02.123Z", "views": 5, "likes": [25], "dislikes": []}}, {"model": "blogs.blog", "pk": 15, "fields": {"title": "Demo by bikash1", "slug": "demo-by-bikash1-15", "category": 4, "author": null, "featured_image": "image/upload/v1770638024/fz9nyhjpvv46hwvbltc0.png", "short_description": "demo by bikash1", "blog_body": "<p>demo by bikash1</p>", "status": "Published", "is_featured": true, "created_at": "2026-02-04T12:58:43.997Z", "updated_at": "2026-02-09T12:00:22.365Z", "views": 9, "likes": [25], "dislikes": []}}, {"model": "blogs.blog", "pk": 16, "fields": {"title": "Asdf", "slug": "asdf-16", "category": null, "author": 25, "featured_image": "image/upload/uploads/2026/02/05/not_install.png", "short_description": "asdf", "blog_body": "", "status": "Draft", "is_featured": false, "created_at": "2026-02-05T01:14:07.958Z", "updated_at": "2026-02-05T01:14:07.966Z", "views": 0, "likes": [], "dislikes": []}}, {"model": "blogs.blog", "pk": 17, "fields": {"title": "1", "slug": "1-17", "category": 2, "author": 25, "featured_image": "image/upload/v1770637999/vwvpujeja0zuyee84dx8.png", "short_description": "1", "blog_body": "<p><img alt=\"\" src=\"/media/uploads/2026/02/09/not-install.png\" style=\"height:1140px; width:1920px\" /><img alt=\"\" src=\"/media/uploads/2026/02/05/not-install.png\" />1</p>", "status": "Published", "is_featured": true, "created_at": "2026-02-05T11:02:22.548Z", "updated_at": "2026-02-09T11:53:46.005Z", "views": 4, "likes": [1], "dislikes": []}}, {"model": "blogs.blog", "pk": 18, "fields": {"title": "7 Blogs That I Totally Enjoy Reading Every Day", "slug": "7-blogs-that-i-totally-enjoy-reading-every-day-18", "category": 1, "author": 40, "featured_image": "image/upload/v1770859796/z0oh1owxaifrane9mdvl.png", "short_description": "Over the past few years, I’ve moved away from following primarily recipe blogs to spending my time enjoying other types of lifestyle blogs, and it has been awesome. I have blog categories on Feedly fo", "blog_body": "<p>Do you have a handful of blogs that you follow&nbsp;purely for fun?</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Over the past few years, I&rsquo;ve moved away from following primarily recipe blogs to spending my time enjoying other types of lifestyle blogs, and it has been awesome. I have blog categories on&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.feedly.com/\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">Feedly</a>&nbsp;for photographers I admire, cool people working for social justice, interesting perspectives on faith, DIY stuff I actually want to try, you name it! Mostly they&rsquo;re just blogs that have nothing&nbsp;to do with recipes, and I find that I look forward to reading them more than ever. But that said,&nbsp;the blogs in my reader that get the most clicks by a landslide are in my favorite category that I have oh-so-creatively named &mdash; get ready for it &mdash; &ldquo;fun&rdquo;.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>And they are just that &mdash; blogs I find fun! Some I have followed for years and years, some are pretty new to me. Some deal with 100% light and fluffy stuff, some dig a little deeper into the meat of life. Some of them share the most beautiful prose, some are random and chatty and full of incomplete sentences. But I love them all, and can genuinely say that I look forward to reading them most mornings (after I read&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.theskimm.com/?r=b27854c8\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">The Skimm</a>, of course, which I&rsquo;m still obsessed with), and also genuinely&nbsp;admire each of the bloggers behind them. &hearts;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>So if any of you are on the prowl for some new non-recipe blogs, I thought I&rsquo;d share 7 of my favorites with you today. I&rsquo;m guessing you&rsquo;ll be familiar with a few, but I&rsquo;m hoping&nbsp;there might&nbsp;be a few&nbsp;new gems in there for you to discover. And hey &mdash; if you have some favorites of your own, pretty please share them in the comments below, because I totally want to check &rsquo;em out.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Have &ldquo;fun&rdquo;!</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"http://designformankind.com/\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"Blogs I Recommend | gimmesomeoven.com\" src=\"https://www.gimmesomeoven.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/Screen-Shot-2016-03-21-at-11.59.58-AM-e1458579627797.png\" style=\"height:303px; width:600px\" /></a></p>\r\n\r\n<h3><a href=\"http://designformankind.com/\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">Design For Mankind</a></h3>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>What It Is:&nbsp;</strong>A lifestyle blog by&nbsp;<a href=\"http://designformankind.com/about-erin/\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">Erin Loechner</a>, filled with beautifully-written essays on everything from design to parenting, marriage, work, travel and more.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Why I Love It:&nbsp;</strong>I&rsquo;ve never met Erin before in person, but she feels like such a kindred spirit. I have enjoyed tuning into her blog for years (like, so many years now!) for a dose of real-life inspiration and lovely prose. Her posts on navigating motherhood and marriage have always been some of my favorites. But I have always especially connected with her posts on slowing down, creativity, and self-care, probably because they&rsquo;re always words I need to take to heart myself. I really admire how open she has been to letting her career evolve and pivot in some big ways over the past decade, and I can&rsquo;t wait to follow along wherever the next roads may lead.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Recommendations:&nbsp;</strong>Every single post in her&nbsp;<a href=\"http://designformankind.com/category/life/\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">Life</a>&nbsp;archives. All of the links at the bottom of&nbsp;<a href=\"http://designformankind.com/2015/12/best-of-2015/\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">this post</a>. The&nbsp;<a href=\"https://livefashionable.com/product/the-able-scarf/\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">Live FashionABLE scarf</a>&nbsp;that she designed.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><a href=\"http://cupofjo.com/\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"Blogs I Recommend | gimmesomeoven.com\" src=\"https://www.gimmesomeoven.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/Screen-Shot-2016-03-21-at-11.54.10-AM-e1458579456751.png\" style=\"height:351px; width:600px\" /></a></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><a href=\"http://cupofjo.com/\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">A Cup Of Jo</a></h3>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>What It Is:&nbsp;</strong>A lifestyle blog by&nbsp;<a href=\"http://cupofjo.com/about/\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">Joanna Goddard</a>&nbsp;covering everything from style to food, design, travel, relationships and motherhood.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Why I Love It:&nbsp;</strong>This is another long-time read for me and one that I still completely look forward to tuning into daily. Her posts are always interesting and fun, and I always look forward to her weekend list of links. Also of note &mdash; she has really awesome readers, so the comment sections on her posts are always worth scrolling.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Recommendations:&nbsp;</strong>Her Friday link posts. Her &ldquo;<a href=\"http://cupofjo.com/category/motherhood/motherhood-around-the-world/\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">Motherhood Around The World</a>&rdquo; series. All product recommendation lists (see her&nbsp;<a href=\"http://cupofjo.com/category/style/\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">style</a>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<a href=\"http://cupofjo.com/category/design/\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">design</a>&nbsp;categories, although heads up that you&rsquo;ve gotta click fast on the links &mdash; her readers regularly buy out the items she loves). Everything on&nbsp;<a href=\"http://cupofjo.com/category/relationships/\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">relationships</a>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<a href=\"http://cupofjo.com/category/motherhood/\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">motherhood</a>.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><a href=\"http://eliseblaha.typepad.com/\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"Blogs I Love | gimmesomeoven.com\" src=\"https://www.gimmesomeoven.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/Screen-Shot-2016-03-21-at-11.53.50-AM-e1458579444944.png\" style=\"height:392px; width:600px\" /></a></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><a href=\"http://eliseblaha.typepad.com/\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">EnJOY It</a></h3>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>What It Is:&nbsp;</strong>A lifestyle and DIY&nbsp;blog by&nbsp;<a href=\"http://eliseblaha.typepad.com/\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">Elise Blaha Cripe</a>, full of&nbsp;<em>tons</em>&nbsp;of great inspiration for all things DIY (memory-keeping, home decor, knitting, photography, recipes, gardening), great resources for blogging and entrepreneurship, and an honest peek into daily life with her husband and two cute kiddos.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Why I Love It:&nbsp;</strong>I have been following Elise&rsquo;s blog since before I even knew what a blog&nbsp;<em>was.</em>&nbsp;(Yeah, way back before blog readers, she was a favorite &ldquo;bookmark&rdquo; in my browser!) &nbsp;And in that weird way that the internet brings people together, I kind of feel like we&rsquo;ve &ldquo;grown up together&rdquo; over this past decade. It&rsquo;s been fun to watch her transition from life as a single graphic designer to falling in love and getting married, having one daughter and then another, taking the leap from one creative endeavor to another to another &mdash; and sharing stories and reflections and photos of it all on her blog along the way. I just really dig the way she thinks about and appreciates life, and love her style. Now if only I could make myself finish a scrapbook&hellip;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Recommendations:&nbsp;</strong>Every single&nbsp;<a href=\"http://eliseblaha.typepad.com/golden/current-projects.html\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">project</a>&nbsp;in her archives. Her posts on&nbsp;<a href=\"http://eliseblaha.typepad.com/golden/small-business-archive.html\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">small business</a>&nbsp;(<a href=\"http://eliseblaha.typepad.com/golden/2015/01/small-business-resources.html\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">these resources</a>&nbsp;are great)&nbsp;and&nbsp;<a href=\"http://eliseblaha.typepad.com/golden/blogging-tips-archive.html\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">blogging</a>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<a href=\"http://eliseblaha.typepad.com/golden/goal-setting-creativity-archive.html\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">goal-setting</a>. And just generally, any posts where she chats about&nbsp;<a href=\"http://eliseblaha.typepad.com/golden/ejbc/\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">everyday&nbsp;life</a>. :)</p>", "status": "Published", "is_featured": true, "created_at": "2026-02-12T01:30:26.818Z", "updated_at": "2026-02-12T01:30:26.830Z", "views": 2, "likes": [], "dislikes": []}}, {"model": "blogs.blog", "pk": 19, "fields": {"title": "Development of a Dynamic Blogging Platform Using Modern Web Technologies", "slug": "development-of-a-dynamic-blogging-platform-using-modern-web-technologies-19", "category": 6, "author": 1, "featured_image": "", "short_description": "This blog documents the journey of two 7th semester IT students, Samir and Bikash, as they design and develop a web-based Blogging System for their final year project, showcasing planning, development", "blog_body": 